                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12556805" author="bryanduxbury" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2008 02:02:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you suggest what exactly you&apos;d like to see change in the way the REST servlet is started? What advantages do you gain?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12556806" author="bien" created="Tue, 8 Jan 2008 02:06:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Currently I can&apos;t specify a config to the hbase rest servlet.  The hbase command line script only looks at hbase-config.sh in the same directory as hbase.  I&apos;d like to be able to specify an arbitrary location for my hbase-env.sh and hbase-site.xml files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12558693" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2008 17:48:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch to make rest and thrift do same as master and regionserver so both can be started/stopped via hbase-daemon.sh and logs go into files named for daemon in $HADOOP_LOG_DIR (I&apos;d attached it previous to 2593, but that&apos;d been close).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12558694" author="stack" created="Mon, 14 Jan 2008 17:49:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Passing via hudson (Passes tests locally)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
